Given the importance of preserving edges during noise reduction, our pipeline will include nodes that can specifically target Gaussian noise. We aim to include a node that applies anisotropic diffusion, which is a well-known method for edge preservation and can be effective in reducing Gaussian noise. This method works by iteratively applying a diffusion process that favors edges over noise, gradually reducing the noise while maintaining the structural details of the image.

